Digital Summit 2020

Thanks to everyone who joined our community of digital professionals for a transformation experience across government at Digital Summit 2020.

The Digital Summit is over for another year. We're already planning for 2021 – register for updates to hear about sponsorship, exhibition and speaking opportunities, and to keep up-to-date with Digital Summit news.

4 days – 4 themes

We dedicated each day of our 4-day program to one of 4 themes:

  • Disruption and Change – Day 1, Tuesday 10 November
  • Human-centred Services – Day 2, Thursday 12 November
  • Leadership and People – Day 3, Tuesday 17 November
  • Technology and Data – Day 4, Thursday 19 November
View program Get updates on Digital Summit 2021 opportunities

Adapt. Engage. Deliver.

Adapt

Adapt to and navigate change in your workplace. Our speakers, presenters and workshop facilitators are driving real change and transformation in their organisations to adapt to our changing world.

Engage

Engage with and learn from our speakers and your peers. Challenge how you think and explore new ways to understand user needs and build solutions.

Deliver

Deliver solutions to real users. Build networks and develop practical actions and plans. Get insights into how some of the biggest organisations are delivering digital transformation, from success stories to valuable failures.

Australian Government Digital Awards

This year the Australian Government Digital Awards were part of the Digital Summit 2020.

We presented the finalists and winners on:

  • Tuesday 10 November – Outstanding digital product or service awards
  • Thursday 12 November – Excellence in partnerships awards
  • Tuesday 17 November – Individual professional contribution awards.
